Privacy Policy
Protecting your privacy is important to us. Therefore, we want to be transparent about the privacy practices we follow. Take a moment to read and familiarize yourself with our privacy policy.
Information Collected
Our application does not collect personal data from users. However, we use third-party services to provide features. These services are detailed below:
1.
Advertising Services:
Our application uses advertising platforms such as AdMob and others, which may collect anonymous information about your activity to display personalized ads. This data includes general browsing statistics and is not directly linked to your identity.
2.
Location:
To enhance the user experience, our application may use your approximate or precise location. This is done solely for statistical, personalization, and advertising purposes. Additionally, our application might not be available in certain locations due policies the location.
3.
Firebase:
We use Firebase, a Google platform, for functions such as usage statistics, notifications, and analytics. Firebase may process technical information about the device anonymously to enhance the application functionality. You can review Firebase's privacy policy for more details.
Use of Collected Information
Since we do not collect information directly, we do not process or use personal data for any purpose.
Data Security
Data is not encrypted:
If information is transferred, it is not done through an encrypted connection.
Data cannot be deleted:
Since we do not collect or store personal data, there is no option to request the deletion of information.
Usage Limitations
To ensure the proper functioning of our application and provide you with an optimal user experience, we have implemented measures to detect certain configurations that may interfere with the application functionality. These measures include:
VPN detected:
The use of a VPN may affect the connectivity required to display relevant ads and other essential application functions. If we detect an VPN, we may ask you to disable it in order to continue using the application.
Emulator detected:
Our application is designed for real devices. The use of an emulator may cause unexpected errors and affect application quality. If we detect an emulator, we may ask you to use a real device to continue using the application.
Private DNS detected:
This setting may block key services such as ad loading. If we detect Private DNS, we may ask you to disable it in order to continue using the application.
Authorization
Our application allows access through biometric technology (fingerprint or facial recognition), ensuring that only users authorized by the operating system can enter. The application does not collect, store, or share biometric data.
Content Accuracy
The materials available in the application come from external sources, such as third-party websites and translator and/or fan communities, so we do not guarantee their accuracy. These materials are provided solely for your convenience.
Protection of Minors
If you are an emancipated minor, have the consent of your legal guardian or tutor, or are of legal age, you can use the application. Although we have implemented protection measures, such as blurring images, we cannot guarantee that all content is completely free of sensitive material. If this is not the case, please do not use the application.
Sensitive Content
We have taken measures to censor or blur images that may contain sensitive content. However, we cannot guarantee that all images are fully censored. By using the application, you accept that we are not responsible for the display of such content.
Sharing Information
We do not sell, share, or otherwise transfer your personal information to third parties, except as described in this privacy policy. We may share information collected in an anonymous and aggregated form with third parties, such as advertisers or business partners, for analysis or market research purposes.
GDPR Compliance
Starting January 16, 2024, we comply with the requirements of the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) set by the European Union for the collection, use, and protection of personal data of users from the EU and the UK. We use a Google-certified Consent Management Platform (CMP) to collect your consent before displaying ads to users from the EU and the UK.
DMCA Compliance
We respect the intellectual property rights of others and are committed to complying with the Digital Millennium Copyright Act ("DMCA"). We encourage you to read our copyright disclaimer available in our disclaimer to learn more. If you have any questions or concerns about our privacy policy, please contact us at:
contacto@heymundomx.com
.
Updates and Modifications
We reserve the right to update or modify this privacy policy at any time. Any significant changes will be communicated to users through an application update or other reasonable means, as applicable. We recommend that you periodically review this policy to stay informed of any changes.
